caption: We met with friends at this restaurant for lunch. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. The staff members were very polite and we had an excellent feeling. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant a lot and we will visit this place again. we highly recommend this place.
Good sausages and chicken salad, people drink beer here
Would surely recommend trying out this place. Awesome mood, flavorful food, awesome customer service. Great work.

This restaurant is unquestionably one of the tastiest place to eat in the region. Always when I come there I am extremely satisfied. They always keep their very high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they give. You can never go wrong with this restaurant. Highly  recommended.
Tried this place before with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I enjoy the awesome mood and tasty food and beverages. 5 stars.
I regularly stop getting some food in here. I like the efficient service and well prepared dishes. Great work.
Incredibly delicious german cuisine. Go for happy hour and get some pretzels and beer. Or sit down for a lovely dinner. You won't be disappointed.
Amazing place

This is definitely a hidden gem. Fast and friendly service. Delectable food. My wife and I shared the chicken schnitzel sandwich. Their bread was fresh light and fluffy. Very juicy and crispy chicken. A 10 for us.
This spot never disappoints. They have fresh food for reasonable prices, there no long wait even when the place is full.
A favorite after rehearsal spot, D.C. Concert Orchestra. Small touch of Europe with American Immigrant attitudes! careful.
Cafe Mozart is awesome. Christmas wouldn't be Christmas if I couldn't stop by and raid the holiday cookies and desserts they have. I send them to a lot of very happy relatives.

I sent my friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The meals are yummy and the team is generous and cooperative. always when we visit this place we enjoy a pleasing time.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.
Great traditional food, cozy place.

awful. I ordered Jaeger Schnitzel which i wanted Pork. I got a barely baked piece of chicken with some dreadful gravy over it. No Cordan Blue because of Virus menu.You should say that on your website. My wife had to get a burger at a German  restaurant.Sad. Worse German food we have ever eaten.We will not be back.
The caffe experience was fantastic! We loved it😜
Great german deli.
The food and service were above our expectations. I really liked the environment of this spot. Nice spot to take my family out for dinner.
This spot is worth a try. They serve large portions for affordable prices. Constantly clean and with excellent vibes. Would recommend to others.
I get to eat here a lot since I work in the area. I got to say their service is always excellent and they keep the spot clean constantly. Pricing is fair and they serve large portions.
They serve large dishes and for convenient rates. very kind staff members. They never disappoint.
Good German food with amazing grocery attached.
Exceptional and delicious food, I loved the vibes the spot has, and the employees were nice. I will surely visit here when I’m around.

Yesterday was the first time we visited this excellent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last. We passed a splendid evening with the courteous service, with the exceptional  food and wine and with the comfortable cost. We will definitely return there again.
I really enjoyed their dishes. I always get excellent service there. The place is well organised and the cashiers are always helpful. Would recommend to others.

German restaurant Mozart. The famous composer was born in Austria however like the Vienna schnitzel. 😉 Whats in a name or nationality..... What a good meal we had and at lunch time. If we would have been seated in the diningroom it would have been 5 stars.
Love this place.  Please support this place or they won't be able to stay open due to COVID-19.
I used to be a server here. Great food! Great atmosphere! Great drinks & a great variety of German & Austrian beer plus more! I live in another state now but planning my visit soon!
Cooked fries just right

This place is so good! The restaurant is hidden behind a small german market but once you get to your seat, there is a sweet little underground atmosphere. The food and service were both great. I got the viennese schnitzel, which was flavorful and crunchy. The potato salad was some of the best i’ve ever had and my dad said the sausage sampler was equally notable. The red cabbage also left a punch! Unfortunately we were not there on a night with live music, but as the only patrons present on the night we ate there, did not mind just listening to the mozart they played on a stereo. On the way out we even bought some german chocolate bars which were a nice end to our meal.

Hidden Gem! You walk into an authentic grocer with tasty treats and down through a small bar and then into a cozy dinning room. The food is delicious and freshly made. The atmosphere is pleasant and staff very helpful. Worth the price. Only critique was the dessert. I had the hazelnut torte and it had no flavor. I had a wonderful experience though.
The food is consistently well prepared and delightful, employees hands over excellent service. I like the cleanliness and ambience. Will visit here again.
Delicious food & lovely service
Good wine!

I used to go here when I worked nearby.  The food is good and the beers come in some large sizes.  This place is always a good time.  The front has a nice bakery and an assortment of European goods including chocolates.
Had dinner here tonight for the second time!  Love it very much and would also recommend to any one!!! Thank you for the amazing dinner!!
Omg the bar in the back...! Love!

Came by this spot for Sunday Brunch. Not super occupied early in the morning so it was great for conversation. The food was excellent! Huge portions. Our server had great recommendations. You really can't go wrong with anything on the menu because they offer a lot of modifications. Definitely check out the authentic candies and such in the mini Mart on the way out.
I had a superb  at this spot. We loved the great atmosphere and the menu. The waiters were very friendly. I’m content we ultimately managed to visit here.
Best German food for a good price in the area. Also features a small shop in front and a fun bar crowd.
Good food
Vegetarian options are par for the course, nothing worth going out of your way for.
Good Authentic selections at fair prices. Live traditional music. Beer by the litre. Highest Recommendation.
Good food, good beer, good prices, and not flooded with TVs.
I liked the Washington Burger with real bacon & the original Mozart Music.

All around an amazing place: excellent, classic food, great beer and great service. Waitress successfully convinced my friend to order the "boot" of beer. Unapologetically 80s ambience, which is a good thing. Will be back as often as possible.
Good food, great service
Cute little spot with live piano (went on a Saturday). Food was good if you’re familiar with German food. The German cake was delicious.
One of my favorite spots to eat. great location, neat, and excellent service. A must try!

Cafe Mozart is the oldest woman-owned restaurant in Washington, D.C. Since 1964, they have been serving the community German and Austrian food. Today, it's expanded into many things. When you walk into the space it's obvious it's a no-frills space. To your right is a coffee area and ice cream stand with a few tables to enjoy our snacks/food at. To your left and in front of you is a German store with all the Milka chocolate bars you can imagine and a bakery selling cakes, pastries, etc. There's also a deli that makes the best-fried chicken schnitzel sandwich for $8. In the way back is the bar and the actual restaurant.
Very clean and welcoming spot. They offer generous meals and for reasonable rates. I enjoyed the menu a lot and the staff members were super amiable and informative. Recommended.
Good food, and one of the few places in DC to get spaetzle.
Food was good and as authentic as you can get.. could have been a bit hotter on the plate. The cakes are outstanding!
Great tucked away German restaurant. They have good food and beer, but only get the 1 liter glass boot of beer. The large boot is to much for one person.

A real hidden gem. It is in the back of a small German grocery store. A little humble place with lots of tables, live walk-around accordion music, generous Austrian/German dinner options, nice bar, and very good food, desserts, and service. I liked it a lot!

Visiting DC my first time, and I felt very displaced. Psychologically I wasn't making the transition and I found myself anxious and uncomfortable. Once I went into this restaurant (passing the entrance which is the cafe)....I felt like myself again. I was comfortable and happy. The food was also reasonably priced and stellar quality. All this food, around $50! My "cultured" (lol) friend says the mustard was the best he's ever tasted. I enjoyed the pumpernickel and seeded rye bread as well. If this place was around my home town, it would be our new date night place.
Small restaurant serving some really delicious food. Sausage sampler and cabbage were fantastic.

Unfortunately I was seated in the back dining room. I normally sit at the bar. I tried to order a Reuben BUT they refuse to serve it in the dining room...only the bar even though there was no seating available. No consideration for the desire of the customer. I won't be back. While the food is good I don't appreciate not being able to order what I can here for. Now der nobody sits in the dining room with the odd accordian player!
Best German restaurant in Washington DC
This place always delivers. They serve awesome dishes for fair rates, there is no waiting time even when the spot is loaded.
Delicious food and great beer!
I always go for lunch at least once when visiting the city
Nice German deli and pastries. I'll have to try the restaurant next time.
Great German food

Do not order from them online. A month later, no products received, no communication from them (despite me reaching out multiple times), finally received a refund today after reaching out again (no note or apology of any kind with the refund). So much for a special Christmas surprise.
Best authentic German cuisine in D.C.
The food was just ok, the accordion player was wonderful

We like a lot eating out. Yesterday we came to this excellent restaurant which we didn’t know before. We enjoyed a delightful experience there with great cooking and  an experienced team and an impressive  chef. We put this place in our phone list  and we will no doubt visit again very soon.  Highly recommended.

Very well organised and convenient restaurant. They provide generous portions and for fair prices. I enjoyed the meals very much and the staff members were super welcoming and informative. I recommend this place.
This place is worth a try. They have big portions for fair prices. Always neat and with excellent atmosphere. Will come back again.
(Translated by Google) The best  (Original) El mejor

I came there for lunch with my girlfriend. Gulasch was nice the cheese fondue was average. The Mozart cake was delicious. The beer variety didn't impress me to much. We loved the small German grocery store which is next to the restaurant, also the lady was nice.  When we left the restaurant the waiter followed us out on the street and put us to speech. We thought maybe we had forgotten something - but no the waitress asked if we liked the service we said yes, then he explained us he expected 15% of tip and the $5 are not enough for a satisfied customer. We were shocked. My girlfriend lived for more than 10 years in the US - never experienced something like that before. Me as a tourist traveling around the world also never seen something like that before. Also we couldn't remember any note on the bill or the menu that they expect at least 15% of tip. If they want the tip they should just add it to the bill automatically, like other places do it. Actually every penny of tip was to much after what happened. It's sad how people can be. We won't go there again and we won't recommend this place to our friends.
Nice atmosphere. Good food.
When I'm downtown I always stop by and have lunch.

I love this café/market. So many different takes on traditional German meals. They even import some German items like Knödel and fruit juice filled German gummy bears (with less food additives too because of European laws).
The food is wonderful, the service is great, and you can find Germany foods you can't get anywhere else here

This restaurant is certainly one of the tastiest restaurants in the area. Whenever I come there I am deeply happy. They manage their very high  level service and the topmost level of dishes  they give. You surely will enjoy this this place. Highly  recommended.
Awesome service. The sausage sampler was great. I am not a big fan of sauerkraut but this was great. I really liked the red cabbage also. My wife had the chicken schnitzel it was fantastic also.

What a hidden gem! This place has everything: deli, ice cream and coffee bar, small mart for European delicacies and chocolate, a pub, and a restaurant. I frequent this place every lunch break and get a bratwurst or a sub from the deli counter. The folks that work there are always nice and welcoming and I’ve heard many compliments from other customers in my time spent dining here. A one stop shop for some delicious food.

From the moment  you arrive in this place  team give you a comfortable feeling. Very courteous stuff, it is a lovely place to hang out with buddies or with your date. Excellent  food, qualified  chef, honest  pay and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
One of my preferred spots to grab some food. great location, always clean, and great service. Very good job!
The place offers a large variety of fresh food. I love eating here. The employees are always welcoming, rates are affordable and the spot is always kept clean.

Nice quaint cafe with deli in the front and restaurant in the back.  Had the special of the day, which was described as a German hamburger.  It was two grilled beef patties with some excellent spices mixed in, and served on a potato pancake that was delicious.  Overall, the food was very tasty, and I will go back to try some sausages and spaetzle.
Awesome environment and very friendly service. The meals were crisp and enchanting. Will surely recommend this restaurant to my friends. Reasonable rates and large meals. Keep up the great work.

We enjoy hanging out. Last night we went to this fine place which friends told us about. We passed a lovely experience there with great dishes and an efficient stuff and an impressive cook. We put this restaurant in our list  and we shall definitely go again very soon.  Highly recommended.
Good bratwurst
All kinds of comfort food here. Great chocolates for after-meal treat.

Had made reservation to eat at Cafe Mozart on November 28th, Thanksgiving.  They waited until 3:15 the afternoon before Thanksgiving to inform us they wouldn't be open.  Really?  Didn't you know you had let reservations be made?  Couldn't you have informed us sooner of your mistake instead of leaving us high and dry for Thanksgiving?  Had expected better.
Good food, but the ambiance is a little stuffy and old fashioned
Very cool setting. Quiet and comfortable with very large beers. Lunch menu food was competent, but unimpressive. Haven't tried main entree options.
Secret German Bar
Live accordion music was fantastic and the food was absolutely delicious.
This place never disappoints, food is great, beer on point (German beer on tap), and the service is always wonderful. Hidden gem in DC worth a visit.

The atmosphere and service were excellent. Something was missing from the food though. I cannot describe it, but other German food I've had was more flavorful. I would recommend this place, but haven't tried other options in the area.  The accordion player was fantastic and really talented.
Food is great.
Never been

Saw Cafe Mozart as I was walking to dinner and realized I hadn't had German food for a while.  I caught them right at the end of a busy stretch and it took a few minutes to clean up a table but it was worth the wait.  Solid German food with the exception of the spaetzle which is among the best I've ever had.  I would recommend to anyone who is in the mood for good food for very reasonable prices in an unpretentious setting.
Sat at the bar. 2 to 9 happy hour, Liter drafts, excellent food and excellent service.
Mmmm delicious german food. The only downside is sometimes the piano is very loud.

My mom is from Germany. So looking forward to my first visit.  Sauerbraten was average. Didn't see my waiter again till I was finished with my meal and I finished my only beer when the meal was half finished.
Best authentic German we've had in a long time!
Very good food and had a nice ambiance
Great food
Great bit of Duetschland in DC! Awesome desserts! I had the Hungarian Sausage with red cabbage. Was excellent! Highly recommend this place for a visit.
Not the typical food I would eat but visiting my son at college and this was his pick.  Food was authentic and good.  It was an old school restaurant in the back of a deli/store. Waiter was great.
Great food. Terrific service. Excellent pianist. Old world ambience. Great value. We'll be back!

I had the Mushroom Schnitzel while husband had the Beef Roulade. Both were delicious. The Mushroom Schnitzel was a giant plate that came with cucumber salad, tomato salad, carrot salad with raisins, three beans salad, and cabbage salad. It didn't look pretty, especially near the end when all the sauces were getting mixed, but everything tasted great and had good texture.

Food and customer service is always great. I used to go there once a week for lunch when I worked close, now I take the metro and get dinner to go. Having lived in Germany for nine years It's good to have them close by. I have been going there for 8 years now. Highly recommend it.
My go to German restaurant in D.C.
Food is authentic and well prepared , the live classical piano music makes it a perfect place to eat

I hate to do this, but here it goes.  Last Sunday I placed an order from the deli.  I received an email stating that the order was received.  Then, nothing. Five days later I called to find out if my order was shipped and was told that someone would call me back with details.  Nothing.  Today I called again and was told to call the deli in a few minutes because the person in charge is not in right now.  No, I will take your number and call you back.  No, I am sorry about this and we will do everything we can to get this order to you.  This is very disappointing.  Maybe someone will read this and respond to me? It is order number 1463.
(Translated by Google) German cuisine is different. Sorry.  (Original) Deutsche Küche geht anders. Sorry.
The food is amazing!  The sauerkraut is so awesome!  Even if you dislike sauerkraut, give it a taste.  It is NOTHING like Americanized processed canned/jarred sauerkraut. :)
Nice restaurant and good German deli.
In the takeout area, when they aren’t rude, they are bizarrely indifferent to your patronage.
This place always delivers. They serve great dishes for fair pricing, there are no long waits even when they are loaded.
Great hidden gem.

(Translated by Google) Very rich food and beer, the person who plays the accordion very friendly and fun. It is a discreet place that I found. By chance  (Original) Muy rica la comida y la cervesa, la persona que toca el acordion muy amable y divertida. Es un lugar discreto que encontré. Por casualidad

Very nice place with great ambiance and great food. Prices are fair, portions are huge, and quality is top. We went on a Wednesday, there was a very sweet old lady playing the accordion and singing German folk songs. Highly recommended.
Had a awesome old school German bratwurst with some sauerkraut it was delicious lol
One of those quirky old DC classics - check it out before a massive chain takes its place.
Vunderbar! Enjoyed all the food and beer. Spaetzle was so fresh! We can't wait to go again and eat more. Very nice and clean. Nice date night
Awesome authentic German food.
Quirky, good food and an accordion player.
It's ok
I had the Berliner w/ sauerkraut and German potato salad..  Very good and I'm stuffed.  Great service. Danke Schön
Great as always. Been going and taking folks since Day 1
Great service and authentic German cuisine!!!!
Great drink sizes
Be careful, the food is so good and the portions are so large that you just might gain weight. I will definitely return!!
This place clearly knows how to treat their clients. Consistently with a nice demeanor. The food is reasonably priced, constantly flavorful and neat.

We enjoyed this little German Cafe. The German food seem to taste like what I remember of my grandparents cooking. Unlike several other places the sauerkraut was cooked to Perfection not overdone or undercooked. Schnitzels are exceptional, and the red cabbage is very good. We will definitely return here for supper.
Fantastic German cuisine. Everything was delicious. They also have a deli where you can purchase German sausages and sides.
Delicious, authentic Beef Roulade. Perfectly seasoned red cabbage. Great German beer on draft.
Very tasty, very filling. My German husband was satisfied with the food. I was happy that they had vegetarian options. The Spätzle is really good!
This is our go-to place in DC
A bit pricey. The food was decent but could be served a bit more appealingly. The bread was a bit stale.
Try the spatzli appetizer. Next time I will probably do with the sausages rather than sauerbraten.
Excellent ice cream and wonderful looking sweet creations adorned the glass case of the market at the front of this restaurant.  Visiting the restaurant later.  A hidden German Restaurant

(Translated by Google) Great discovery in Washington, 100% German food, good service and correct price.  (Original) Gran descubrimiento en Washington, comida 100% alemana, buen servicio y precio correcto.

Looking for Sausages?  Look no further. Cafe Mozart has a great selection, if you aren't sure where to start I recommend the Hungarian Kielbasa.  Their in-house hot sauce is tremendously hot. Use sparingly if you don't enjoy breaking out in sweat as you eat, but it's worth it.  Note: Walking in looks like some sort of convenient store/deli, just keep walking because the restaurant is towards the back.

Unbelievably good German food.  Everything was expertly prepared.  I had the sausage and Kasseler, red cabbage, sourkraut, potato salad and a side if spaetzle.  We shared apple strudel and chocolate cake for dessert.  Everything was fantastic.

This is my new favorite place in DC. The food was great! We got the family meal and asked the server to pick a few choices for us. He picked some things I wouldnt have picked for myself like the carrot raisin salad and it actually wasnt bad. My favorite  was the red cabbage with the bratwurst. The chicken schnitzel was also delicious. The service was great and the food came quickly. Very happy we found this place!

I work at the bank an we have little to no time for food runs. I love these guys and ladies that work here. Call in your order an 15 mins it's ready if it's a quick meal. Their wings & fries are the best and their mocha chocolate cake ladies are to die for.

If you love German food, you're going to love Cafe Mozart. We ordered the Viennese Schnitzel and Goulash and took the recommendations of our server. We were so glad we did. Dinner was so amazing we ate every bite.!! Make sure you put this place on your Must Do list.
Good beer, good brats
The best Austrian cuisine in the DC area, hands down, and excellent entertainment provided by Stella.
Delicious food, but menus online claim they serve breakfast when they don’t anymore. Great bartender and very authentic food, even vegetarian options!

Get all the cake. It's a quirky place, dessert/coffee to the right, German/scandanavian supermarket to the left, Austrian/German restaurant and bar in the back. I've been frequenting it for 8 years now and it hasn't missed a beat. Also, all the cakes are pretty much amazing. We take out slices on a monthly basis. Not because we need them, no. They just are that addictive.
Great food, great atmosphere.
Excellent German food, HUGE beers!!
Nice but only two waitresses!
The whole meal was delicious and seemed very authentic. The service was great. Would recommend to others looking for something a little different!
Great experience, authentic tasting, try the dark beer! Friendly staff, will definitely go back when in town again ¡¡¡
When Warsteiner highlights your beer menu, then mediocrity in food is bound to follow. Too bad, German food has so much potential if done well.
I enjoy coming here every time that I am in Virginia. Great place to be with the family.
Ate here tonight.  Food was very good.  Some of the best red cabbage I've ever eaten.  Nice atmosphere and the woman playing the accordion was an absolute delight.

(Translated by Google) Very disapointed. Dark place. Grocery certainly interesting but for coffee a place of fast food style, cutlery and plastic cup ... coffee to take oneself and bad, the restaurant not accessible for a tea and everything at the bottom. I did not find this place friendly at all.  (Original) Très déçue. Endroit sombre. Épicerie certes intéressante mais pour le café un endroit du style fast food, couverts et gobelet en plastique...café à prendre soi-même et mauvais, le restaurant non accessible pour un thé et tout au fond. Je n'ai pas trouvé cet endroit convivial du tout.
(Translated by Google) Very good coffee and succulent Sachertorte biscuits  (Original) Très bon café et succulent biscuits Sachertorte
Best coffee in D.C. ! Lived in Germany for 30 years, forget Starbucks, their coffee has true taste!
Best German food in DC!
Great food. Good service
Great food, great service finally, great ambiance.
One of the last remaining DC classics....
Great service, good food.
Great place for a fresh, cold German beer. Recommend the mixed sausage plate.
My favorite place in town. Great food, awesome huge beers
Good chow

Excellent German food, but it was not easy to find. It was in the back of a grocery store.  Our uber driveisdef it twice. Once inside, tho the food was fantastic.  It's so hard to find good authentic German food. Was very impressed. Wait staff was top notch.
Great food and the market has great stuff
Delicious authentic German food
Brilliant German cuisine!
Interesting little shop with a lot of hard-to-find German and European brands. Has a $5 minimum for credit card purchases.

Nice assortment of (what I think is) authentic German dishes. Disappointed that menu online and menu in restaurant showed a nice Austrian red wine that the waitress claims is no longer available. Had to settle for a generic cab sauvignon by the glass. Tablemates really enjoyed the beer assortment.

Great place for dinner. Food is excellent German food with several choices. I had a sausage sampler plate with five types and it was excellent.  There was a pianist who played Mozart all night which was very pleasant.  The beer is good with choices on draft in several sizes including a boot.  Service was very good.
Good food!! German fare and professional sevice.
Any place with Warsteiner on tap is okay by me.  Excellent sandwich too.
Awesome food, service!
Excellent dining experience - good German food.
Good food.
Outstanding service.  Have some tiramisu!
Most authentic German food...great service! Loved it plus lots of German speciality foods also for sale chocolate coffee etc. I'll be back!
This place is in our top 5 best places we've ever eaten. Incredible food, incredibly nice service.
A hidden gem.  Delicious authentic German/Austrian food.  Hole in the wall fun atmosphere.  Nice selection of German draft beer.
Cafe Mozart is our family's favorite German/ Austrian restaurant in DC. We enjoy the restaurant the most when we get to hear live music. The food is delicious. We like the deli.in the front as well.
Restaraunt and grab n go paztries, cakes, and ice cream too! Great stop after walking back from the monuments on your way back to the hotels.
Canceled my GrubHub order after ten minutes. Said they were “too busy.” If you’re too busy, turn off GrubHub before hungry people order from you and wait ten minutes.

Love this place, mostly because of the giant beers and the grocery out front, but the food is good too. They have been cutting corners on the food lately (but haven't raised prices), but like I said, the giant liters of German beer are my big draw. The service is always impeccable and the place is always clean and well run.
Fantastic!  Authentic food.  Great service.   And the lady who plays the accordian (and wooden spoons--- Wednesdays and Thursdays) is super fun.
Unique little spot for German food and drinks with live piano classical music. They have a German food market as well.

Has a German market up front where you can stock up on chocolates, spices, wursts, cheeses, cakes and other German specialties. In the back is a small restaurant with a small menu of German foods. The owners are very friendly. I always stop when I'm in DC to get a few pieces of Shane torte, (German style cheesecake). It's the only place outside of Germany that makes this delicious dessert that my Tante use to make.

An easy to miss spot. But well worth the hunt, for the great authentic German food, German beer, and European centric attached market. if you're in the mood for a great bratwurst and even better sauerkraut this is your place.

Great German quality food! The brat was tender and had delicious flavor.  Sauerkraut was spot on! The potato salad was not too onion-y.  The only thing I didn’t care for were the beers on tap they had.  But I don’t like IPAs so I know many of the beer aficionados... so take that with a grain of salt :)  it is a very small place for eating (it’s all the way in the back) so MAKE A RESERVATION!  Photos as of April 2019
Cool experience

Unpleasant, bordering-on-surly old white guy bartending. Apparently he takes new customers totally for granted. That's a shame, bc based on some unique features, this place could build a serious following - IF the ppl who work there cared. For now, Cafe Mozart is a place you will mot mind totally missing. DC has several Austrian/German themed bar/restaurants that treat customers much better than this place. Also the better ones don't feature dumpy retail stores in front with zero employees to help customers, and old merchandise about to expire (because it's not moving).
The food was good, but I really liked the setup of the deli/bakery in front, and the restaurant in the back.
Fast and unique. Loved the accordion player---a very talented, sweet woman from Austria. Definitely worth a visit.
The owner is extremely friendly and helpful. He helped us out in a toothy situation. Great restaurant AND great store!
Great food and atmosphere

Fantastic food, wonderful service. Their German sausages are delicious and it’s just so refreshing to have authentic German food here in the Capitol. By far, top three German restaurants that I’ve been to.
Nice beer

I'm not a German food expert and this was pretty much my first Reuben but I thought it was really great. The bread was buttered and toasted perfectly. The corned beef was filling but not piled so high that you can't take a bite. The potato salad was also delicious. I wish I had taken a photo of my meal but I just wanted to eat it right away.
Authentic German

Great place for some German beer and authentic German food!  We had a large party and they were very accommodating not only with the tables but the chef let is order everything family style.  The kids had fun and traditional burgers and ice cream.  I highly recommend this spot for the food, beer and did I mention German groceries?  They have it all.  Very authentic.

Unexpected hidden taste of Germany in DC. We tried and approved: the venison steak, schnitzel (pork Viennese style), and sausages sample. All plates are very generous, there is no need for appetizers. The true home European style are the sides: carrot salad, cucumber salad, red cabbage, sourkraut, and potatoes that turned to be a crispy pan fried. Only one desert we had room to try was a piece of Sacher torte. It was the only weak spot of our dinner. It has not much in common with the cake that is served in Sacher hotel or Demel in Vienna.
Always a great meal!  Warm atmosphere, love it when the pianist is there as well

You need to walk through a charming little german deli, then nestled in the back is the restaurant. Great traditional German food. Our servers are always attentive and friendly. We go for lunch most Friday's and have a great time. They serve beer in pitchers which is a rare thing in most DC restaurants.

This restaurant is an annual tradition for my father and I; we've been going for more than five years now. Every time the place is clean, cozy, and well-appointed and the staff are friendly and intimately familiar with the menu.  The food is outstanding. This place has never served us anything that wasn't top-notch and we always leave completely satisfied. The beer selection is always excellent and the waitstaff is very helpful in making a good choice for your tastes and menu choice. Wonderful restaurant for lovers of traditional German food. Walk through a German deli and you'll find a full restaurant tucked into the back with wonderful, rich authentic German cuisine.  The food is the star of the show here - the menu has everything you would expect, a big selection of German and Eastern European sausages, schnitzel, goulash, dumplings, potato pancakes, etc. etc. And all of it is good!  We shared the family style dinner for two, which lets you split three entrees and three sides from a list. We had the chicken schnitzel, the beef goulash, and two sausages for our entrees, plus red cabbage, spaetzle, and the German potato salad with bacon as our sides. Everything was terrific! The goulash was rich and hearty, with tender chunks of beef, perfect for eating alongside the spaetzle; the potato salad was fantastic, incredibly well-balanced sweetness and acidity complemented perfectly by bits of bacon. The only things we weren't enamored of were the two desserts we got - hazelnut cake and apple strudel - both of which were fine but didn't blow us away. Between the two, pick the strudel (or try one of the many other desserts on offer, maybe you will find a gem that we haven't yet!)  Service was extraordinarily friendly, helpful, and quick. We had a lovely experience with our server.  The vibe of this place is old school - fairly brightly lit, white tablecloths, traditional decor. This is the opposite of a trendy establishment, it feels like a throwback from 20 or 30 years ago. But none of that is to say it was a negative vibe at all - honestly some might even see it as a nice change of pace from the dozens of loud, tightly-packed industrial barns lit by Edison bulbs that you're sure to come across as you explore DC's contemporary dining scene. When we were there, there was a live accordion player during dinner, adding to the traditional feel of the place - she was great, and to add to the authentic feel, I even overheard her chatting in German with another table between songs.  Pricing is moderate, but not inexpensive. Entrees are mostly in the $16-22 range. The family style shared meal was $35/person, for which you really get an enormous amount of food.  As nondescript and non-hip as this place is, in the Metro Center area behind a deli, I was worried it would be dead. Happily, there were a number of other tables there enjoying what Cafe Mozart has to offer. We will be back to join them, hopefully we'll see you there!

Hidden gem. Deli was neat and offered a selection of lovely sweets. Waitress was kind and accommodating. The decor was nice and the live entertainment was an awesome bonus. The food was OUTSTANDING. Schnitzel, rouladen, and potatoes were some of the best I’ve ever had. Dessert was yummy; I’d recommend any of them. The prices weren’t bad, especially for D.C. Definitely will return :)

To get to the restaurant area, you must first walk through a small shop, where you can stock up on all your German snacks and ingredients.  The restaurant area is cozy, with live German folk music on many evenings, which adds to the atmosphere.  On my most recent visit, I had one of the family style set menus, with your choice of three main dishes and three sides.  Everything about it was absolutely delicious.  I've also had the sausage platter and schnitzel; all are great.  Finally, don't drive yourself, because the evening isn't complete without a 2-liter Das Boot, though they also sell beer in one liter and half a liter for the light weights.  They have their menu online, so you can check out their offerings and prices.  Schnitzels are in the $20s and the set menu is $35/person.  Das Boot will set you back $25.
